<div class="headCo">

# <span>Iterations: OMLoop</span>

<div class="headCo_co">

<div>

<div class="infobloc">

<div class="txt">

|                                                                                   |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| <span class="iconButton_tim">![omloop2\_icon.png](../res/omloop2_icon.png)</span> | A great number of compositional operations, be they basic or more complex, are **iterative processes**. This is the case, for instance, of transposition, combinatorial manipulations, scale building, and so on. Such processes can be designed in OM via a specific tool : the **OMLoop module** . |

</div>

<div class="caption">

<div class="caption_co">

![controlmenu.png](../res/controlmenu.png)

</div>

</div>

<div class="txt">

The OMLoop module is available in the `OM Kernel / Control` menu.

</div>

<div class="linkSet">

<div class="linkSet_ti">

